description: Sum of two (possibly negative) cubes in at least 4 ways.
comments: This sequence is infinite, since if n is in the sequence so is n*k^3 for all k > 0; thus a(n) << n^3. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Nov 29 2014
prog: (PARI) T=thueinit('z^3+1);is(n)=my(v=thue(T, n)); #v>6 && #select(u->u[1]<=u[2],v)>3 \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Nov 29 2014
author: _Colin Mallows_
